Professor Czeisler’s recommendation is that students think about putting one alarm to go to bed and another to wake up, and be aware of the harmful effects of the “blue light” emitted by the screens of electrical appliances and LEDs, which can alter circadian rhythms, so they would end up having trouble falling asleep.
